#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:2
msgid "set_color - set the terminal color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:7
msgid "set_color [OPTIONS] [VALUE]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:12
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:14
msgid ""
"``set_color`` is used to control the color and styling of text in the "
"terminal. *VALUE* describes that styling. *VALUE* can be a reserved color "
"name like **red** or an RGB color value given as 3 or 6 hexadecimal digits "
"(\"F27\" or \"FF2277\"). A special keyword **normal** resets text formatting "
"to terminal defaults, however it is not recommended and the **--reset** "
"option is preferred as it is less confusing and more future-proof."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:19
msgid "Valid colors include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:21
msgid ""
"**black**, **red**, **green**, **yellow**, **blue**, **magenta**, **cyan**, "
"**white**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:22
msgid ""
"**brblack**, **brred**, **brgreen**, **bryellow**, **brblue**, "
"**brmagenta**, **brcyan**, **brwhite**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:24
msgid ""
"The *br*- (as in 'bright') forms are full-brightness variants of the 8 "
"standard-brightness colors on many terminals. **brblack** has higher "
"brightness than **black** - towards gray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:26
msgid ""
"An RGB value with three or six hex digits, such as A0FF33 or f2f can be "
"used. A three digit value is equivalent to specifying each digit twice; e."
"g., ``set_color 2BC`` is the same as ``set_color 22BBCC``. Hexadecimal RGB "
"values can be in lower or uppercase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:30
msgid ""
"If :envvar:`fish_term24bit` is set to 0, fish will translate RGB values to "
"the nearest color on the 256-color palette. If :envvar:`fish_term256` is "
"also set to 0, fish will translate them to the 16-color palette instead. "
"Fish launched as ``fish -d term_support`` will include diagnostic messages "
"that indicate the color support mode in use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:34
msgid ""
"If multiple colors are specified, fish prefers the first RGB one. However "
"if :envvar:`fish_term256` is set to 0, fish prefers the first named color "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:37
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:39
msgid "**-f** or **--foreground** *COLOR*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:40
msgid ""
"Sets the foreground color. This is equivalent to calling ``set_color COLOR`` "
"with the exception that the keyword **normal** will only reset the "
"foreground color to its default, instead of all colors and modes. It cannot "
"be used with *VALUE* or **--print-colors**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:44
msgid "**-b** or **--background** *COLOR*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:45
msgid "Sets the background color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:47
msgid "**--underline-color** *COLOR*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:48
msgid "Set the underline color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:50
msgid "**-c** or **--print-colors**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:51
msgid ""
"Prints the given colors or a colored list of the 16 named colors. It cannot "
"be used with **--foreground**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:54
msgid "**-o** or **--bold**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:55
msgid "Sets bold mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:57
msgid "**-d** or **--dim**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:58
msgid "Sets dim mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:60
msgid "**-i** or **--italics**, or **-iSTATE** or **--italics=STATE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:61
msgid "Sets italics mode. The state can be **on** (default), or **off**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:63
msgid "**-r** or **--reverse**, or **-iSTATE** or **--reverse=STATE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:64
msgid "Sets reverse mode. The state can be **on** (default), or **off**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:66
msgid ""
"**-s** or **--strikethrough**, or **-sSTATE** or **--strikethrough=STATE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:67
msgid "Sets strikethrough mode. The state can be **on** (default), or **off**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:69
msgid "**-u** or **--underline**, or **-uSTYLE** or **--underline=STYLE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:70
msgid ""
"Set the underline mode; supported styles are **single** (default), "
"**double**, **curly**, **dotted**, **dashed** and **off**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:72
msgid "**--reset**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:73
msgid ""
"Reset the text formatting to the terminal defaults before applying the new "
"colors and modes. This is equivalent to calling ``set_color normal`` except "
"that it is possible to set the foreground color in the same call (e.g. "
"``set_color --reset green``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:76
msgid "**--theme=THEME**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:77
msgid ""
"Ignored. :ref:`Color variables <variables-color>` that contain only this "
"option are treated like missing / empty color variables, i.e. fish will use "
"the fallback color instead. :doc:`fish_config theme choose <fish_config>` "
"erases all :ref:`color variable <fish_config-color-variables>` whose value "
"includes this option, and adds this option to all color variables it sets. "
"This allows identifying variables set by a theme, and it allows fish to "
"update color variables whenever :envvar:`fish_terminal_color_theme` changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:85
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:86
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:89
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:91
msgid ""
"Using ``set_color normal`` will reset all colors and modes to the terminal's "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:92
msgid ""
"In contrast, ``set_color --foreground normal`` will only reset the "
"foreground color and leave all the other colors and modes unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:93
msgid ""
"Because of the risk of confusion, ``set_color --reset`` is recommended over "
"``set_color normal``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:94
msgid ""
"Setting the background color only affects subsequently written characters. "
"Fish provides no way to set the background color for the entire terminal "
"window. Configuring the window background color (and other attributes such "
"as its opacity) has to be done using whatever mechanisms the terminal "
"provides. Look for a config option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:95
msgid ""
"Some terminals use the ``--bold`` escape sequence to switch to a brighter "
"color set rather than increasing the weight of text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:96
msgid ""
"``set_color`` works by printing sequences of characters to standard output. "
"If used in command substitution or a pipe, these characters will also be "
"captured. This may or may not be desirable. Checking the exit status of "
"``isatty stdout`` before using ``set_color`` can be useful to decide not to "
"colorize output in a script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:99
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/set_color.rst:104
msgid ""
"set_color red; echo \"Roses are red\"\n"
"set_color blue; echo \"Violets are blue\"\n"
"set_color 62A; echo \"Eggplants are dark purple\"\n"
"set_color normal; echo \"Normal is nice\" # Resets the background too"
msgstr ""
